# DoDone1.0

1.debug:type wrong number in dfinish, it's steal count to finish
2.add:dtomonth dtoyear task, but can have no count
3.new file tree:
	DoDone-	LICENSE

		README.md(including how to use it)

		setting		/	set task in week
				/	format:
				/		WEK 	-all this week will add task
				/		Mon	-all Monday will add task
				/		Tue	-all Tuesday will add task
				/		Wed	-all Wednesday will add task
				/		Thu	-all Thursday will add task
				/		Fri	-all Friday will add task
				/		Sat	-all Saturday will add task
				/		Sun	-all Sunday will add task

		update-log	/log all version and updates

		bin-		Sortfile:
					1.if dfinish : judge whether can finish, or report error
					2.or else finish a task and sort
					3.or else add a task and sort
				Show:
					1.report about 'dday/dmonth/dyear'

		bash-		dadd:	
					1.check whether exist the path $PATH/usr/dtask/dday/ and file, or report error
					2.read the new task and add it, and alter the information in $DPATH/usr/
					3.log the operation
				#dclean:
				#	1.debug and clean all just ok
				dfinish:
					1.check whether exist the path $DPATH/usr/dtask/dday and file, or report error
					2.read the task number and check whether it is right, if not report error
					3.sign it, and alter the information in $DPATH/usr/
					4.log the operation
				dnew:	
					1.check and establish paths "$DPATH/usr" and all file in it
					2.establish "$DPATH/usr/dtask/." and initialize it
					3.log the operation
				dshowd:
					1.show the day
				dshowm:	
					1.show the month
				dshowy:	
					1.show the year
				dtoday:
					1.check whether exist "$DPATH/usr/dtask/.", or report error
					2.show today task
				dinit:
					1.check the file "$DPATH/setting", and establish and initialize it
					2.read from $DPATH/setting and update the today task file
					3.log the operation

		.usr-		log	/log all operation in bash

				.showtmp	/showtmp

				dday-	dnlog	/log file name
					all-	/file
					finish-	/file

				dmonth-	dnlog	/log file name
					all-	/file
					finish-	/file

				dyear-	dnlog	/log file name
					all-	/file
					finish-	/file

				dtask-	dday-	/file
					dmonth-	/file
					dyear-	/file
				
